    {
      "fieldname": "customs_rules_help_html",
      "fieldtype": "HTML",
      "label": "Customs Rules Help",
      "options": "<div style=\"padding:8px 0 4px;line-height:1.55;\"><p><strong>How each rule is used.</strong></p><p><strong>Tariff Number</strong>: optional exact HS/customs code match.<br><strong>Custom Material</strong>: matches Item Custom Material from the article workbook's <code>DOUANE MATERIAL</code> column.<br><strong>Value Per Kg</strong>: declared customs value per kg.<br><strong>Rate Percent</strong>: customs percent applied to the declared customs value.<br><strong>Sequence</strong>: tie-breaker when multiple matching rules exist. Lower sequence wins.</p><p><strong>Formula</strong><br><code>Customs Fee = Value Per Kg x Total Kg x Rate Percent / 100</code></p><p><strong>Example</strong><br>Custom Material <code>ACIER</code>, Value Per Kg <code>13</code>, Total Weight <code>100 kg</code>, Rate Percent <code>25</code><br><code>Customs Fee = 13 x 100 x 25% = 325</code></p><hr style=\"margin:10px 0;\"><p><strong>Customs Value Delta Tax</strong></p><p>When <strong>Apply Tax On Customs Value Difference</strong> is enabled, Orderlift calculates an additional tax on the <em>delta</em> between the item's declared customs base value and its buying cost.</p><p><strong>Delta</strong> = (Value Per Kg × Total Weight) − (Qty × Unit Buying Price)<br>If <code>delta &le; 0</code>: no delta tax is applied.<br>If <code>delta > 0</code>: delta tax is charged on the excess.</p><p><strong>Delta Tax</strong> = Delta x Tax Rate / 100</p><p>Tax Rate is taken from <strong>Tax Template</strong> if set; otherwise from the <strong>Company's Default Sales Tax Template</strong>.</p><p><strong>Example</strong><br>Value Per Kg = <code>13</code>, Total Weight = <code>100 kg</code>, Unit Buying Price = <code>2</code><br><code>Customs Base Value = 13 x 100 = 1300</code><br><code>Delta = 1300 - (100 x 2) = 1100</code><br>Tax Rate = <code>20%</code><br><code>Delta Tax = 1100 x 20% = 220</code><br><strong>Total Customs = 325 + 220 = 545</strong></p></div>"
    }
